        Rootwalker moved to the spring and, a moment later, returned with water cupped in their root-hands, offering it to me. The gesture surprises me—quiet care delivered without words.

        I say, "Thank you."

        Rootwalker nodded and moved away to check the path ahead.

        Leafwhisper says, "Rootwalker is very good at anticipating needs—doesn't talk much but always pays attention—excellent guide, really—we've worked together for many journeys and I've learned to read their actions—when they stop suddenly it means obstacle ahead—when they adjust pace it means terrain difficulty changing—very reliable communication once you learn the patterns—"

        I drink the cool water and grin.

        I say, "Buddy, this is like Mav's first day on the Seven Valleys journey—Season three, episode two."

        Buddy says, "You're right! The one where he meets the guide who never stops talking?"

        I say, "Yes—and the silent one who just leads!"

        Buddy says, "Leafwhisper and Rootwalker are perfect casting!"

        Leafwhisper's leaves rustle with curiosity. Leafwhisper says, "You're comparing us to a story?"

        I say, "The best story. You'd love Uncharted. Mav is this explorer who—"

        I say, "Buddy, how does the network communication work across long distances? Chemical signals seem like they'd be slow."

        Buddy says, "I've been wondering that too!"

        Leafwhisper practically vibrates with enthusiasm. Leafwhisper says, "Wonderful questions! So the primary fungal networks can actually transmit information quite rapidly through electrical signals along the mycelium—"

        The explanation is fascinating. I find myself leaning forward to listen.

        Rootwalker returns and says, "Time."

        I stand eagerly. I say, "More?"

        Leafwhisper rustles: "Back to it then! The next section goes through a particularly beautiful grove—"

        I say, "I can't wait!"

        They walk.

        Step—step—step. The afternoon blurs into a delightful rhythm: Leafwhisper explaining everything—plants, terrain, network protocols, interesting rocks.

        Buddy asks, "How do different species coordinate priorities?"

        Buddy asks, "What happens when network signals conflict?"

        Buddy asks, "Does the fungal network ever get congested?"

        Leafwhisper loves having two enthusiastic listeners.

        Rootwalker says, "Left here—root system—slow—rest soon."

        Scout explores and returns, explores and returns, endless energy. At one point Scout investigates a steep bank to the left, then bounces back to me with a different rhythm—not the curious bounce, something more urgent. I watch Scout check the terrain again, return, bounce insistently, then bound ahead toward what I can see is more stable ground.

        They are showing me the path.

        ¶

        That's not random exploring— that's scouting.
